The paper discusses the use of deep learning for music information retrieval, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also focuses on the comparison of different deep learning architectures and transfer learning strategies, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with the representation of music data, which is a topic that falls under the subcategory of signal processing (cs.SD).
